solution.p:
The location of the diffraction minima on the screen can be deduced from the right-angled triangles.  Let the y-axis be pointed up on the screen, then we will have

	y = (50\ \textrm{cm})\ \tan\theta.

Denote the positions of the four minima by y_{+1}, y_{-1}, y_{+2} and y_{-2}.

	 \amp y_{\pm 1} =  (50 \textrm{cm})\ \tan\theta_{\pm 1} = \pm 14\ \textrm{cm}
	 \amp y_{\pm 2} =(50 \textrm{cm})\ \tan\theta_{\pm 2} = \pm 33\ \textrm{cm}
